    "name": "ASTM F1717 Compression-Bending Verification Method Requirement",
    "description": "Per the V&V 40 credibility framework and the pre-submission agreement with FDA, the primary validation activity supporting QoI comparison for construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement SHALL be conducted as a controlled experiment. This requires that boundary conditions, loading rates, specimen preparation, and environmental parameters be fully prescribed and independently randomised across both participating laboratories, with blinded measurement collection to eliminate observer bias. The controlled-experiment designation is necessary to satisfy the inference chain from bench observation to model acceptance at Model Risk Level 3.",
    "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment"
  },
