      "name": "Lab 1 ASTM F1717 Compression-Bending Comparison — Stiffness and Yield Force",
      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness and yield force were compared against six non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested at Laboratory 1 under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending conditions. Mean stiffness error was 4.2% and mean yield force error was 6.8%, both within the pre-established 10% acceptance bound. The E/uval metric was 1.31, satisfying the E/uval < 1.96 criterion. The laboratory followed standard ASTM F1717 protocol; specimens were sourced from a single production lot and tested sequentially on a single test frame. Technician notes and ambient temperature logs were collected alongside force-displacement traces. This observational data collection approach is well-established in the orthopaedic device literature and provides high-quality QoI measurements that directly support the model comparison.",
      "passedAcceptanceCriteria": true,
      "quantityOfInterest": "construct stiffness, yield force",
      "errorMetric": "E/uval = 1.31",
